    "Typical implementations include Gaussian Mixture Model -Hidden Markov Model (GMM-HMM) frameworks and later Deep Neural Network (DNN-HMM) hybrids [6], [45], which formed the foundation of many large-scale ASR toolkits such as Kaldi [46] and CMU Sphinx [47].",
    "Early SLU systems adopted the ASR → NLU pipeline [4], [48], where natural language understanding models operated on 1-best or N-best ASR hypotheses to perform tasks such as intent classification, slot filling, and dialogue state tracking [49]."
